The paper deals with private information retrieval protocols, which are commonly studied in the computer security (cs.CR) and information theory (cs.IT) communities. The paper also discusses the tradeoffs between privacy and efficiency, which are relevant to the database systems (cs.DB) and distributed systems (cs.DS) communities. Lastly, the paper proposes new schemes based on partitioning, which are related to the algorithms and complexity (cs.CC) community.
